<TITLE> Aviation secy Syed Zobair dies, aged 54 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 25 (bdnews24.com)Civil aviation secretary Syed Zobair died at the age of 54 on Wednesday, as life-support was withdrawn at a Dhaka hospital. Zobair was declared clinically dead Tuesday night by the United Hospital authorities, where he was admitted on Feb 27 with heart trouble. A civil servant of the 1979 batch, Zobair began his career in the industries ministry. He was promoted to secretary while at the water resources ministry. He joined the ministry of civil aviation and tourism as secretary on Feb 25, 2008. Zoabir received his BA (Hons) and MA in English language and literature in 1974 and 1975 from Dhaka University. Born in 1955 in a Natore village, Zobair leaves behind a son and a daughter. bd
